  the boundary conditions on quark lines are dictated by the lattice gauge theory (LGT) and fulfil a sort of orthogonality constraint such that, whenever the quark and antiquark lines coincide, the effective string vanishes . This forces the adimensional radius $nu = sqrt(pi sigma) R_t$ to be exactly $nu = 1/4$.
